Enable CreateMergeReturnPass unconditionally in the performance optimizer
pipeline (not just for Metal).

Upstream filament only runs CreateMergeReturnPass when TargetApi is METAL,
because MergeReturn breaks Tint conversion (WebGPU output) and has historically
tripped bugs on some AMD macOS and Adreno drivers. Sneeze/Halogen doesn't target
WebGPU and isn't affected by those specific driver issues, so we enable the pass
for every target. Result: the SPIR-V inliner (CreateInlineExhaustivePass, run
immediately after) actually inlines non-tail-return functions instead of
leaving thousands of call sites un-inlined and emitting one "could not be
inlined" warning per site. Material compiles become quieter, downstream passes
process smaller SPIR-V, and shipped shader binaries are smaller and more
portable across mobile drivers that can't re-inline what desktop drivers can.

Target: libs/filamat/src/GLSLPostProcessor.cpp, registerPerformancePasses (the
non-Metal optimizer pipeline used for regular material compiles). NOT
registerSizePasses -- that's a separate, rarely-used size-optimization pipeline.

--- a/libs/filamat/src/GLSLPostProcessor.cpp
+++ b/libs/filamat/src/GLSLPostProcessor.cpp
@@ -1073,7 +1073,7 @@ void GLSLPostProcessor::registerPerformancePasses(Optimizer& optimizer, Config c
 
     RegisterPass(CreateWrapOpKillPass());
     RegisterPass(CreateDeadBranchElimPass());
-    RegisterPass(CreateMergeReturnPass(), MaterialBuilder::TargetApi::METAL);
+    RegisterPass(CreateMergeReturnPass());
     RegisterPass(CreateInlineExhaustivePass());
     RegisterPass(CreateAggressiveDCEPass());
     RegisterPass(CreatePrivateToLocalPass());
